Three models for ADF test       
model 1:$\Delta X_t = \delta X_{t-1}+\sum _{i=1}^{m}\beta_{i}\DeltaX_{t-i}+\epsilon_t$          
        model 2:$\Delta X_t = \alpha+\delta X_{t-1}+\sum _{i=1}^{m}\beta_{i}\DeltaX_{t-i}+\epsilon_t$          
        model 3:$\Delta X_t = \alpha+\beta t+\delta X_{t-1}+\sum _{i=1}^{m}\beta_{i}\DeltaX_{t-i}+\epsilon_t$          
        $H_0:\delta = 0$,that means there exist a unit root or nonstationary.Stare from model 3,until model 1.Once one model reject $H_0$,it can be considered as a stationary series.